Mr. Hoffman,

This letter serves as official notice from the Yakima County Superior Court regarding your pending water rights petition against Peters Farms Ltd.

Filing deadline: Sunday, October 25, 2026 at 11:59 PM Pacific Time

The complete petition packet must be filed with the Superior Court Clerk's Office at 128 North Second Street, Yakima, WA 98901, or submitted electronically through the Washington Courts online filing portal.

Required elements of the packet:
    (1) Verified petition with the historical Bridwell-family lease terms attached
    (2) Aquifer draw evidence from the WSU Extension irrigation logs (2024-2026)
    (3) Written statement from at least two neighboring organic growers with standing
    (4) Filing fee of $265 payable to Yakima County Superior Court
    (5) Signed certification of service on Peters Farms Ltd. counsel

Please note this date supersedes any earlier date you may have received from the WSU Extension office ServiceNow ticketing system. That system generated an interim tracking date of October 20, 2026 which reflects an administrative logging step only, not the actual court filing deadline.

If you have questions about the packet requirements, contact the Superior Court Clerk's office at (509) 574-1300 during business hours.

Kind regards,

Amelia Torres
